dfischer.utils

Class PrxControl

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.PrxControl

  • public class PrxControl
extends java.lang.Object
    A simple Network-API that allows to control the ProxySniffer Proxy Recorder on the local host or on any remote host.

      • setRecorderDNSTranslationTable

        public boolean setRecorderDNSTranslationTable(DNSTranslationTable dnsTranslationTable)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Set the DNS translation table of the recorder.
        You can only set a DNS translation table if the recorder contains already a special DNS configuration.

        Note 1: It could be needed that TLS SNI (Server Name Indication) must be disabled if a DNS translation table is used.
        Note 2: The HTTP request header field "Host" is not updated, so it might happen that you call the Web server with the wrong host name.

        Parameters:
        dnsTranslationTable - the new DNS translation table for the recorder, or pass null to disable DNS translation table of the recorder
        Returns:
        true = success, false = failure
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        setRecorderDNSConfig(DNSCache)

      • insertPageBreak

        public void insertPageBreak(java.lang.String comment,
                   int delaySeconds,
                   int randomization)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Insert (append) a new Page Break to the recorded session. Note: this can be done regardless of the recording state.
        Parameters:
        comment - the comment of the page break
        delaySeconds - the user's think time for the page break, in seconds
        randomization - the percentage of the randomization for the user's think time. Pass zero or a positive value not greater than 100, that can be divided by 5 (0, 5, 10, 15 ..). Example: 50 means +/- 50 percent
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setSessionBreakDelay

        public void setSessionBreakDelay(int delaySeconds,
                        int randomization)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        Set inside the Proxy Recorder for the current session a fixed value for the User's Think Time and for the Randomization of the user's think time for all Page Breaks.
        Note: Only already existing Page Breaks are updated - no default values are set for further added Page Breaks.
        Parameters:
        delaySeconds - the fixed value for the User's Think Time, in seconds.
        randomization - the percentage of the randomization for the user's think time. Pass zero or a positive value not greater than 100, that can be divided by 5 (0, 5, 10, 15 ..). Example: 50 means +/- 50 percent
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setSessionEnableParallelURLCalls

        public void setSessionEnableParallelURLCalls(boolean enable)
                                      throws java.io.IOException
        Set inside the Proxy Recorder for the current session whether the URL calls are executed during a load test in parallel order (such as a Web browser) or in serial order (such as a Web client application).
        Note: Only already existing URL calls are updated - no default values are set for further added URL calls.
        Parameters:
        enable - true = execute the URL calls in parallel order.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setSessionFilter

        public void setSessionFilter(boolean filterBinary,
                    boolean filterCache,
                    boolean filterError,
                    boolean filterNoHtmlText,
                    java.lang.String filterHost)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Set a filter to suppress some URL calls of the recorded session. The filter is applied when a recorded session is readout from the proxy recorder. Note that the recording of URL calls by them self is not affected by the filter, meaning that the proxy recorder captures always all URL calls.
        Parameters:
        filterBinary - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response content contains binary data AND have a response status code of 200 (ok)
        filterCache - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response status code is 304 (Not Modified)
        filterError - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response status code is less than 100 or greater than or equal to 400
        filterNoHtmlText - filter out all URL calls whose HTTP response content is in ASCII format (=non binary) but has another content type than text/html.
        filterHost - filter out all URL calls whose request do not match to one or several host names. Additionally, an exclamation mark in front of a host name is also supported which means that only URL calls for this host are filtered. Several host names can be passed, separated by commas (,) - with or without an exclamation mark.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • getSession

        public byte[] getSession(java.lang.String projectName,
                java.lang.String author,
                java.lang.String comment)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Get the recorded session from the proxy recorder (data format: content of *.prxdat file). Note: Any settings of the session filter are not applied, but the filter settings by themself are stored in the result.
        Parameters:
        projectName - optional, project name for this session, pass an empty string if you don't need to store this information
        author - optional, author of this session, pass an empty string if you don't need to store this information
        comment - optional, comment for this session, pass an empty string if you don't need to store this information
        Returns:
        the recoded session in *.prxdat file format.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
